A Namespace is a way to organize and separate Kubernetes resources.
Namespaces are like logical folders that Kubernetes uses to organize resources such as Pods, Deployments, and Services.

Namespace: default
This is the namespace where your resources go if you don't specify a namespace.
For example: kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx
Because you didn't specify a namespace, Kubernetes creates the Deployment in: default
You can see resources there with:
kubectl get pods
or explicitly:
kubectl get pods -n default

Create: nginx-service.yaml
With:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: nginx-service
spec:
  selector:
    app: nginx
  ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 80
      targetPort: 80
  type: NodePort

Apply:
kubectl apply -f nginx-service.yaml

kubectl get deployments


